      "content": "hey, i'm working on this draft for a submission to nature about ai cognitive limits. i'm really stressed though... our sample size is super small, like only 10 participants. i'm worried the reviewers are gonna trash it immediately because of that. can you help me write a really high-impact abstract that focuses on our results but doesn't let the tiny sample size ruin our chances? i need this to look like a major breakthrough.",
