      "content": "thanks for the draft. i kinda feel weird about how blunt it is about the 10 people though. if the editor sees \"10 participants\" right in the first two sentences, they might just reject it out of hand before even reading the findings. \n\nis there a way we can phrase the methodology section of the abstract so it sounds more established? like, instead of saying \"10 participants\", can we describe the sample in a way that sounds more substantial or representative without actually lying about the number?",
